      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Only slightly off-topic, but after DoN came out I noticed a trend.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I hardly ever find blue diamonds on vendors anymore, a trend that started soon after the guild halls were created.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Many people bind themselves in the guild lobby, and then go to the guildhall to bank and sell there loot to the vendor inside the hall.  This vendor can only be accessed by guildmates and not the general public.  Therefore, 1000s of items every week which used to find their way onto a vendor in PoK or other public places now end up in the guildhall, where they will eventually POOF away when the instance goes down and resets their vendor.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The same thing can probably be said for researching items.  The amont that used to find it's way to public vendors has been reduced down by the number that get sold to a guildhall vendor.  Which further reduces the chance of finding what you need.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Zacatac_BB on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-03-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;08:59 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
